02:04.516 --> 02:08.561
Sometimes the feelings inside
me get messy like dirt.

02:08.812 --> 02:10.312
And I like to clean things.

02:10.395 --> 02:12.607
Pretend the dirt
is the feelings.

02:13.566 --> 02:15.485
This floor is my mind.

02:16.110 --> 02:19.155
That is called coping.

02:20.906 --> 02:22.200
And the COs don't care

02:22.283 --> 02:23.993
'cause they like things clean.

02:24.076 --> 02:25.077
(SCOFFS)

02:25.203 --> 02:28.414
And that is called symbiosis.

02:29.624 --> 02:31.376
Suzanne, listen.

02:33.586 --> 02:37.048
Those things that
Larry said on the radio?

02:37.882 --> 02:40.259
They sounded a lot worse
than they really were.

02:40.385 --> 02:43.805
And when I said those things to
him, it was before I knew you.

02:44.972 --> 02:47.392
Before I knew what
a nice person you are.

02:50.019 --> 02:52.139
And you have to admit that
you come on a little strong.

02:52.397 --> 02:55.899
It's okay, dandelion.
You know why?

02:56.401 --> 02:58.403
I used to spend
a lot of time thinking

02:58.528 --> 03:00.071
how I could make you love me.

03:00.196 --> 03:02.782
Like, if I had
long pretty hair,

03:02.906 --> 03:05.410
or if I made a chocolate
cake with frosting,

03:05.535 --> 03:07.662
or if I had a green bicycle.

03:07.746 --> 03:11.708
No! You are great
the way that you are.

03:11.791 --> 03:13.376
I know.

03:13.459 --> 03:17.088
Because the answer is,
you're not a nice person.

03:20.675 --> 03:22.468
You're a mean person.

03:22.844 --> 03:26.890
And I used to think you
was a yellow dandelion

03:28.182 --> 03:31.060
but you're all dried up
with the puff blown off.

03:31.143 --> 03:32.937
And it's not your fault.

03:33.062 --> 03:37.066
You are who you are,
like, I am who I am.

03:38.443 --> 03:39.444
I'm not mean.

03:42.363 --> 03:44.741
I didn't mean
to be mean to you.

03:46.576 --> 03:48.870
You gotta start
from the inside out

03:48.953 --> 03:50.955
or else you'll
step on the clean.

04:08.306 --> 04:09.432
Hey.

04:10.099 --> 04:11.976
Look at you,

04:12.059 --> 04:14.604
waking up for crack
of dawn I-told-you-so.

04:14.687 --> 04:15.980
That's dedication.

04:16.648 --> 04:18.149
I have to pee.

04:18.649 --> 04:19.858
But as long as I'm here,

04:19.983 --> 04:22.987
how's that, uh, spontaneous
confession treating you? (CHUCKLES)

04:23.154 --> 04:25.657
Shittier than I thought,
which is impressive,

04:25.740 --> 04:28.159
considering I'm literally
scrubbing toilets.

04:28.367 --> 04:31.078
You're sucking all of the
joy out of my gloat.

04:32.622 --> 04:34.332
You gonna tell me what
happened with the fiance?

04:34.415 --> 04:35.917
Oh, you know,

04:36.000 --> 04:39.545
I accused him of feeding
on my misfortune

04:39.671 --> 04:41.297
with the sensitivity
of a vampire squid,

04:41.422 --> 04:44.509
and then he accused
me of betraying him

04:44.592 --> 04:46.928
in a disgusting, yet totally
predictable manner.

04:47.011 --> 04:48.888
So, we're in a good place.
(SIGHS)

04:49.889 --> 04:51.182
I'm sorry, Pipes.

04:51.599 --> 04:56.521
And that was before
he told me that his father,

04:56.813 --> 05:00.024
AKA my lawyer,
looked at the records

05:00.441 --> 05:06.739
and found out that it was you
who ratted me out to the Feds.

05:11.953 --> 05:13.162
(GATE BUZZES)

05:14.288 --> 05:15.289
Fuck.

05:15.414 --> 05:18.042
Don't worry about it. I
mean, fool me once, right?

05:19.126 --> 05:21.045
Okay, listen...
Alex.

05:22.254 --> 05:24.716
I'm over it. Really.

05:27.760 --> 05:28.928
It's fine.

05:35.393 --> 05:36.686
(INMATES CHATTING)

05:37.186 --> 05:38.187
You got mine?

05:38.646 --> 05:39.939
Caputo's special!

05:52.368 --> 05:54.808
You know, you're not supposed to
take food out of here, Sister.

05:54.871 --> 05:56.915
SISTER INGALLS: Maybe we
can bend that rule a bit.

05:56.998 --> 05:59.625
At my age you, you've got to
keep your blood sugar steady.

05:59.751 --> 06:01.126
I dip at around 10:00.

06:02.587 --> 06:03.922
Don't worry about it.

06:08.634 --> 06:11.345
Oatmeal and cheese
sandwich, no crusts.

06:13.681 --> 06:15.307
You should eat something.

06:17.142 --> 06:18.394
He's coming.

06:23.232 --> 06:26.485
(STUTTERS) I like the
shape of your ears.

06:29.864 --> 06:31.490
What else do you
like the shape of?

06:33.284 --> 06:34.410
(SHUSHES)

06:37.830 --> 06:39.331
You know what I miss?

06:39.457 --> 06:40.792
Mimosas.

06:42.376 --> 06:45.128
I'm gonna need your help
with something.

06:47.090 --> 06:49.508
(MAN SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY OVER PA)

06:50.133 --> 06:51.970
You missed breakfast.

06:52.135 --> 06:54.305
I needed to sleep
more than I needed eggs.

06:56.641 --> 06:58.643
Miss Claudette,

06:58.768 --> 07:01.144
I want to apologize to you for
everything that Larry said.

07:01.270 --> 07:02.480
I had no idea it was gonna...

07:02.605 --> 07:05.149
I know the stories they
say about me, Chapman.

07:05.232 --> 07:07.352
I wish you'd thought enough
of me to ask for the truth.

07:08.820 --> 07:09.988
(SNIFFLES)

07:11.948 --> 07:14.158
If you're getting sick,

07:14.241 --> 07:15.326
please keep your hands clean

07:15.451 --> 07:17.202
and stay on your side
of the room.

07:17.954 --> 07:20.999
Tomorrow is a big day for me
and I won't have you ruin it.

07:21.124 --> 07:22.667
That seems to be
a talent of yours.

07:26.963 --> 07:28.324
You ain't said
nothin' all morning.

07:29.548 --> 07:31.592
There ain't nothing
worth saying.

07:32.217 --> 07:34.018
And they say there's no
such thing as miracles.

07:36.014 --> 07:38.182
Yikes.
No scrappy rejoinder?

07:39.308 --> 07:40.909
They must have put
you on the scary meds.

07:41.519 --> 07:42.880
Why ain't you
throwing back at her?

07:43.021 --> 07:44.563
'Cause there ain't no
point, Leanne, all right?

07:44.689 --> 07:46.231
I got beat.

07:46.357 --> 07:48.651
Ain't nobody up there
looking out for me no more.

07:49.234 --> 07:50.528
I'm looking out for you.

07:50.945 --> 07:52.279
You know,
he finally come to me,

07:52.363 --> 07:54.283
after all this time that
I've been following him.

07:54.323 --> 07:56.450
I finally heard him talk to me,

07:56.534 --> 07:59.537
him saying how I was
his girl, I was.

08:00.788 --> 08:01.956
Turns out it weren't him.

08:02.040 --> 08:03.541
No, it was Chapman,

08:04.042 --> 08:05.751
the bitch devil of Litchfield.

08:06.418 --> 08:08.838
Well, you missed her
boyfriend's crazy radio show.

08:09.005 --> 08:11.132
Hey. Chapman put
her ass on the line

08:11.215 --> 08:13.342
to get you out
of Psych, you know?

08:13.509 --> 08:14.909
She's cleaning toilets
every morning

08:14.927 --> 08:16.261
like Private
"fucking" Benjamin.

08:17.471 --> 08:20.558
Look, I ain't looking
for revenge, okay?

08:22.309 --> 08:24.395
She'd probably
kick my ass anyway.

08:24.562 --> 08:28.273
No way, Tucky. You're
small but you got spit.

08:28.399 --> 08:29.692
Man, do you know what it means,

08:29.775 --> 08:32.528
when there ain't nobody up
there punishing the evildoers?

08:32.904 --> 08:36.032
It means there ain't nobody giving out
prizes for the good ones, neither.

08:36.741 --> 08:39.952
'Cause there ain't no judge,
there ain't no justice.

08:40.078 --> 08:44.749
We just crawl around this Earth
like ants and then we die.

08:50.088 --> 08:52.090
You don't gotta kill it.

08:54.508 --> 08:56.719
I'm just thinking
about you, is all.

08:57.428 --> 08:58.637
(SCOFFS) I mean, you
show 'em a baby,

08:58.763 --> 09:00.283
you get good money
from the government.

09:00.389 --> 09:01.557
(CLEARS THROAT)

09:01.640 --> 09:02.975
Plus WIC packages.

09:04.309 --> 09:06.854
All kinds of things
in them packages you get.

09:06.938 --> 09:09.690
Cheese, peanut butter.

09:11.109 --> 09:12.276
Baby food.

09:13.527 --> 09:16.072
Hell, you can make a good
casserole out of baby food.

09:16.155 --> 09:18.783
Sprinkle some Fritos
on top, tuna.

09:19.575 --> 09:23.996
Tasty as hell, and baby
food is vegetables.

09:24.205 --> 09:25.806
Well, if you're eating
all the baby food,

09:25.915 --> 09:27.708
what's the baby supposed to eat?
(CHUCKLES)

09:30.128 --> 09:31.629
Suit yourself.

09:31.921 --> 09:33.131
I'm not keeping it, Arlen.

09:35.591 --> 09:37.301
You never keep it.

09:37.927 --> 09:39.011
(SIGHS)

09:39.511 --> 09:43.682
Look, my cousin, Sierra, she had a
baby down at County last summer,

09:43.933 --> 09:45.226
and after they drug tested her,

09:45.309 --> 09:46.811
they took the baby boy away

09:46.894 --> 09:50.689
and they arrested her for
endangering a minor, okay?

09:51.523 --> 09:53.818
So, I think babies
are cute and all

09:53.901 --> 09:56.612
but I ain't going
to jail for this fucker.

09:58.156 --> 09:59.991
Well, another idea is,

10:03.077 --> 10:04.495
you could stop doing drugs.

10:09.167 --> 10:10.417
(BOTH SNIGGERING)

10:17.508 --> 10:18.884
(COUGHING)

10:20.970 --> 10:24.056
For real, though, I need a
ride tomorrow to the clinic.

10:26.058 --> 10:29.937
Hell, tomorrow I gotta do
the thing with the hammers.

10:34.150 --> 10:35.526
(URINATING)

10:41.991 --> 10:43.117
Jesus!

10:43.201 --> 10:44.285
Hey.

10:46.787 --> 10:48.497
You know what's overrated?

10:49.623 --> 10:50.875
Toast.

10:55.671 --> 10:56.839
Wanna fuck in the pantry?

10:56.964 --> 10:58.883
Hey!
Get out of here.

10:59.008 --> 11:00.218
You're gonna get us shot.

11:00.592 --> 11:02.011
I'm serious.

11:03.679 --> 11:05.520
I was so afraid about you
finding out the truth,

11:05.597 --> 11:07.225
but now it's out,
and it's okay.

11:07.683 --> 11:09.268
It's kind of a rush.

11:10.228 --> 11:12.104
Cool thing about sex
in an industrial kitchen

11:12.230 --> 11:13.438
is there's a ton
of margarine in here.

11:13.689 --> 11:14.690
Stop it, Alex.

11:14.773 --> 11:15.774
Come on, babe.

11:15.900 --> 11:17.651
Let's celebrate how totally
fine you are with everything.

11:17.776 --> 11:18.861
You're freaking me out.

11:18.944 --> 11:19.987
You ain't seen nothing yet.

11:20.154 --> 11:21.488
I said stop it.
What?

11:21.572 --> 11:23.866
Can't a girl be totally overcome
with desire for someone

11:23.949 --> 11:25.034
who's being so cool,

11:25.117 --> 11:26.160
and so forgiving?

11:26.244 --> 11:27.828
We're not okay!

11:30.413 --> 11:31.665
This is not fine!

11:31.749 --> 11:34.252
Good. Now we could
talk about it.

11:34.417 --> 11:35.457
It that what this is about?

11:35.586 --> 11:37.420
Yeah. That's what this is about.

11:38.089 --> 11:41.259
You find out that I personally
got you thrown in here

11:41.384 --> 11:44.136
at the exact moment your manicured
fingers were like closing

11:44.262 --> 11:45.346
on the yuppie brass ring,

11:45.428 --> 11:47.639
and somehow you don't
have a problem with it?

11:47.765 --> 11:48.933
You are so full of shit.

11:49.100 --> 11:50.393
Fuck you.

11:51.434 --> 11:52.937
Fuck you, Alex.

11:53.562 --> 11:54.855
You want me to be angry?

11:54.939 --> 11:58.109
Well, guess what, I'm really fucking
angry, because I love you, Alex.

11:59.777 --> 12:02.863
I love you
and I fucking hate you.

12:04.156 --> 12:06.284
I have really been trying
to keep my shit together,

12:06.409 --> 12:09.828
but if you really need to see
me Hulk out over this...

12:12.706 --> 12:14.250
Larry left you, didn't he?

12:17.795 --> 12:21.299
And that's why you're
fake-fine with me.

12:22.300 --> 12:24.302
Right now you're willing to
overlook pretty much anything

12:24.427 --> 12:28.055
because ultimately you are
just terrified of being alone.

12:30.849 --> 12:32.851
Is that what I am to you?

12:33.185 --> 12:38.149
A fucking binky for you to
suck on until you feel better?

12:41.193 --> 12:42.361
Look at me.

12:47.450 --> 12:49.034
Why did you do it?

12:49.201 --> 12:51.078
They were offering less time.

12:51.829 --> 12:53.789
A lot less time, depending
on how much I gave them.

12:54.706 --> 12:58.336
I hadn't seen or heard
from you in eight years.

12:58.501 --> 13:02.047
You weren't even real anymore,
which made it easier.

13:03.799 --> 13:06.802
And I was pretty sure one of the
other guys would give you up anyway.

13:06.927 --> 13:10.097
And if I'm being really honest,

13:10.181 --> 13:11.765
I was still pissed at you.

13:13.017 --> 13:14.435
For leaving.

13:15.769 --> 13:16.937
For my mom.

13:18.189 --> 13:22.360
So, yeah, at that moment
I probably was just, like,

13:22.485 --> 13:24.403
"Fuck you," you know?

13:26.905 --> 13:28.366
I'm not proud of myself.

13:28.491 --> 13:30.034
You lied to me.

13:31.202 --> 13:32.953
When I first got here
you could've given me

13:33.037 --> 13:34.288
this whole speech right then.

13:35.706 --> 13:37.708
I wanted you to like me.

13:39.542 --> 13:40.711
I still do.

13:41.504 --> 13:44.882
Maybe you should've thought
that all the way through.

13:57.061 --> 13:58.062
Ugh.

13:58.145 --> 13:59.646
This isn't even
remotely coffee.

14:00.356 --> 14:01.940
No, it's dandelions.

14:02.441 --> 14:04.193
Which are loaded
with potassium, man.

14:04.276 --> 14:06.653
Everyone thinks potassium
is all about the bananas,

14:06.737 --> 14:08.613
but that is
banana-lobby bullshit.

14:12.243 --> 14:13.827
She does have a point
about the radio thing,

14:13.911 --> 14:15.538
I'll cop to that.

14:15.620 --> 14:17.415
She's the most interesting
thing about me right now,

14:17.498 --> 14:19.917
and I used that.
Mmm.

14:20.334 --> 14:22.711
And I guess it was a dick move.

14:22.794 --> 14:25.130
But that doesn't make it
okay that she cheated on me.

14:25.339 --> 14:27.466
No, cheating
is a strong word, pal.

14:28.092 --> 14:30.094
Sorry, is there
another word for

14:30.177 --> 14:32.263
"fucking someone other than
the person you promised,

14:32.346 --> 14:34.223
"in the very recent past,

14:34.306 --> 14:36.016
"to fuck exclusively forever"?

14:36.267 --> 14:38.387
Uh, no. I'm just saying that
this "someone" was a girl,

14:38.436 --> 14:39.603
which isn't really cheating.

14:40.687 --> 14:43.607
Like, you and Piper
play squash together.

14:43.732 --> 14:46.944
And if in her downtime she
joins a softball team, then...

14:47.111 --> 14:49.280
That's the bigger problem
with this whole thing.

14:49.405 --> 14:51.115
She fucked a woman.

14:51.240 --> 14:53.242
So what, is she gay now?

14:54.243 --> 14:59.164
I don't know about "now." I just
think that she is what she is, man.

15:00.499 --> 15:02.000
Which is what exactly?

15:02.167 --> 15:04.336
I'm gonna go ahead and guess
that one of the issues here

15:04.462 --> 15:07.923
is your need to say that a
person is exactly anything.

15:13.304 --> 15:15.306
I think it might be over.

15:20.519 --> 15:21.937
Uh...
No offense, Bloomer,

15:22.020 --> 15:24.773
but it's super weird
that I'm in the middle here.

15:26.024 --> 15:27.304
You know,
one of the main reasons

15:27.318 --> 15:29.278
that I live 110 miles
from civilization

15:29.361 --> 15:31.863
is I'm kind of allergic
to other people's drama.

15:31.989 --> 15:35.033
Including, and sometimes especially
when it involves my sister.

15:35.159 --> 15:37.035
That's kind of the whole point,

15:37.161 --> 15:38.496
you know what I'm saying?

15:39.163 --> 15:42.207
Yeah. I know. Uh...
You want me to take off?

15:42.541 --> 15:45.169
No, man. Absolutely chill
here for a few days

15:45.252 --> 15:46.504
if it helps you out.

15:46.629 --> 15:48.255
I would just really
enjoy not being involved

15:48.339 --> 15:51.300
in any kind
of decision-making process.

15:51.383 --> 15:54.064
And respect the limitations of the septic system.
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

15:54.136 --> 15:55.887
It's touch-and-go
as it is.

16:00.934 --> 16:01.935
Holy shit.

16:03.687 --> 16:05.022
(YELLING)

16:07.191 --> 16:09.109
Everything okay?
Dude, I'm engaged!

16:27.169 --> 16:29.630
Mr. Caputo, I gotta
make a complaint

16:29.713 --> 16:31.674
about the fungus in
the Spanish showers.

16:31.756 --> 16:32.757
Talk to a CO about that.

16:32.883 --> 16:34.163
I did. They told
me to come to you

16:34.218 --> 16:36.637
because you were the only one that
could deal with this from high up.

16:36.720 --> 16:37.721
(SIGHS)
I bet they did.

16:37.804 --> 16:42.393
I got a serious case
underneath my big toenail.

16:43.018 --> 16:47.398
It is all squishy
and green under there.

16:47.481 --> 16:48.566
As a matter of fact,
let me show you.

16:48.691 --> 16:51.527
No. That will absolutely
not be necessary.

16:51.735 --> 16:54.446
Well, could you at least get Crazy
Eyes over to the light brown side?

16:54.572 --> 16:56.990
I mean, she's keeping the ghetto
cleaner than a nun's chocha, mira.

16:57.074 --> 16:59.743
And another thing,
between my pinkie toe

16:59.826 --> 17:02.413
and my ring toe, it is
bad news, bad news!

17:02.538 --> 17:04.415
So when I go to medical
call and I show them,

17:04.498 --> 17:06.250
they write that shit down,

17:06.333 --> 17:08.877
I gotta let them know
that I told you guys.

17:09.086 --> 17:10.671
What happened
to your shower shoes?

17:10.878 --> 17:12.130
So I just passed out
sitting there like that,

17:12.256 --> 17:14.136
and then when I woke up
my zoris, they were gone,

17:14.174 --> 17:15.217
right off my feet.
(VOCALIZES)

17:15.300 --> 17:19.512
Which reminds me, stealing, that's
another problem we've been having.

17:22.391 --> 17:23.752
Well, what are you
gonna do, right?

17:23.767 --> 17:25.269
At least we got our sanity.

17:26.936 --> 17:29.064
Oh, look at that.
Ten of jack.

17:29.398 --> 17:33.611
Mr. Caputo, I think I heard somebody
crying in the utility closet.

17:33.736 --> 17:34.945
Oh, well, we can't have that.

17:35.028 --> 17:37.072
I'm just saying
'cause we had that suicide

17:37.155 --> 17:38.657
and you know
how these girls are.

17:38.782 --> 17:41.410
They get an idea in their heads
and if you don't watch out

17:41.493 --> 17:44.288
they start offing themselves every
time they get their period.

17:44.371 --> 17:46.665
I know you guys wrote a really
encouraging memo about it,

17:46.790 --> 17:47.874
but truth be told,

17:47.958 --> 17:50.544
I'm not sure
everybody here can read.

17:50.628 --> 17:52.630
I mean, I would
look into it myself

17:52.755 --> 17:54.590
but I got too much empathy.

17:54.715 --> 17:55.924
Lays me low.

17:56.091 --> 17:57.842
If I am not home
in my massage chair

17:57.968 --> 18:00.387
holding a glass of Wild
Turkey in 25 minutes,

18:00.471 --> 18:02.431
I am holding you
personally responsible.

18:05.350 --> 18:06.685
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

18:07.561 --> 18:10.981
Yeah. That's it, baby. Faster.

18:11.106 --> 18:12.274
(GRUNTS)

18:12.816 --> 18:14.526
Seriously, faster.

18:15.860 --> 18:17.780
Oh, my God.
Here it comes.

18:17.862 --> 18:22.033
Oh, God! Oh, God!
I, I love you. Oh, God!

18:22.743 --> 18:23.786
(GROANS)

18:23.868 --> 18:25.746
Christ on a cross.

18:27.247 --> 18:28.415
(PANTS)

